y are, and underpinning the scientific method are core principles that can help us all navigate modern life more confidently. Discussing the nature of truth and uncertainty, the role of doubt, the pros and cons of simplification, the value of guarding against bias, the importance of evidence-based thinking, and more, Al-Khalili shows how the powerful ideas at the heart of the scientific method are deeply relevant to the complicated times we live in and the difficult choices we make.Read this book and discover the joy of science. It will empower you to think more objectively, see through the fog of your own preexisting beliefs, and lead a more fulfilling life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2022) 0aSciencexPhilosophy. 7aSCIENCE / Philosophy & Social Aspects.2bisacsh  aAccuracy and precision.  aAnecdotal evidence.  aAppeal to emotion.  aAvailability.  aBehavioural sciences.  aBillionaire.  aBody of knowledge.  aCertainty.  aChemist.  aCognitive dissonance.  aConfirmation bias.  aConspiracy theory.  aConvenience.  aCosmological constant.  aCultural relativism.  aDiscovery (observation).  aEchinus esculentus.  aEducation.  aEfficacy.  aEmpathy.  aEmpirical evidence.  aEveryday life.  aExplanation.  aFact.  aFixation (histology).  aHumility.  aHypothesis.  aIT Works.  aIdeology.  aIllusory superiority.  aInvention.  aKnow thyself.  aLogical reasoning.  aMoral relativism.  aNatural science.  aNature of Science.  aObjectivity (philosophy).  aObjectivity (science).  aObservation.  aPhenomenon.  aPhilosophy of science.  aPhysicist.  aPrediction.  aPrince Charming.  aQuantum mechanics.  aRationality.  aReal image.  aReality.  aReason.  aReproducibility.  aResult.  aScience.  aScientific enterprise.  aScientific evidence.  aS